JOHANNESBURG – An upswing in steel prices helped lift Arcelor Mittal’s full-year top line.
	
	The South African segment of the company’s sales was up by 19-percent for the year ended in December. READ: Metal industry concerned about US pending anti-dumping duty investigation However, the inflation of iron ore and other material prices outweighed the company’s selling prices. This caused the company to move farther into the red, with its annual loss widening from R4,7 billion to R5,1 billion. Thesteelmakerl maker says it continues to lobby government for trade protection initiatives for the key steel-consuming sectors. eNCA